        "solution": "Ghana Vadya. Solid instruments are usually played with a striker or hammer. These instruments are not capable of producing definite pitches that are required for creating a melody. That is why their use is limited in classical music. Tata Vadya - These are Stringed instruments. Avanaddha Vadya - These are percussion instruments. Sushira Vadya - These are wind instruments. The Shehnai is a popular wind instrument in India."
