        "solution": "N-1. Network topology - Arrangement of a network, comprising nodes and connecting lines. There are 6 types of topology, Bus Topology - Every computer is connected to a common bus (single cable), Ring Topology - Every node is connected to two other nodes, forming a loop. Tree Topology - A central root node from which all other nodes branch out, Star Topology - Each device on the network is connected to a central hub, Mesh Topology ({n(n-1)/2})- Each node is connected to every other node in the network, Hybrid Topology - It is a combination of two or more network topologies."
